            <rect x="8" y="8" width="5" height="5" rx="1" fill="#B85C38"/>
          </svg>
          <span>Restoration Mechanics</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="sp-faqx-heading">
          Tuckpointing FAQ<br>
          <em class="sp-faqx-heading-accent">For Property Owners</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="sp-faqx-desc">Clear answers on how we surgically restore failing mortar to protect your asset.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sp-faqx-body">
        <nav class="sp-faqx-nav" id="faq-nav" aria-label="FAQ categories">
          <button class="sp-faqx-tab active" data-cat="problems" aria-selected="true"><span class="sp-faqx-tab-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>The Process</button>
          <button class="sp-faqx-tab" data-cat="cost" aria-selected="false"><span class="sp-faqx-tab-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Materials</button>
          <button class="sp-faqx-tab" data-cat="repair" aria-selected="false"><span class="sp-faqx-tab-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Diagnostics</button>
          <button class="sp-faqx-tab" data-cat="process" aria-selected="false"><span class="sp-faqx-tab-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>AMS Policies</button>
        </nav>
        <div class="sp-faqx-panels" id="faq-panels">
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel active" data-cat="problems" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">How deep do you actually grind the old mortar?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">We grind out a minimum of 3/4-inch to 1-inch of the decayed joint. Anything shallower is a cosmetic band-aid that will fall out after one winter. We grind deep to ensure structural bonding.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Will grinding create a massive dust storm?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">We utilize specialized masonry saws equipped with HEPA vacuums and implement wet-grinding techniques where necessary to dramatically reduce airborne silica, protecting your home and landscaping.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel" data-cat="cost" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Can you match the color of my older, weathered mortar?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Yes. We custom-blend our mortar on-site, using precise dye ratios and specific sand aggregates so the new joints look perfectly weathered and blend invisibly into the untouched areas of the wall.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Why do you analyze the old mortar's strength?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Because putting hard modern cement against a soft historic brick forces the brick to take the brunt of thermal expansion, causing it to shatter. We match the new mortar's compressive strength to the original to protect the brick faces.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel" data-cat="repair" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">How do I know if I need tuckpointing or a full rebuild?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">If the mortar is turning to sand but the bricks are still aligned, tuckpointing will save it. If the bricks themselves are spalling heavily or the wall is leaning, a structural rebuild is required. We evaluate this during our free assessment.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Do I need to tuckpoint the whole house?</button>
              <div class="sp-faqx-a" aria-hidden="true"><div class="sp-faqx-a-inner">Usually, no. Weathering is directional. Often, only the chimney or the wall facing the harsh prevailing winds needs restoration. We only recommend repairing the specific elevations that have failed.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="sp-faqx-panel" data-cat="process" role="list">
            <div class="sp-faqx-item" role="listitem">
              <button class="sp-faqx-q" aria-expanded="false">Will you subcontract my tuckpointing job?</button>
